HEADWORD: Cautioner
<hw>Cau"tion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who cautions or advises.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>A surety or
sponsor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cautionry</ent>⟦br⟧
